{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"Edna de Crichton","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Edna de Crichton","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Edna"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Crichton"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Edna Crichton","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1240–1283","fullLifespan":"Abt 1240–1283","birthDate":"+1240","birthPlace":{"address":"Pathhead, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":55.86667,"longitude":-2.96667,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1283","deathPlace":{"address":"Pathead, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":55.83,"longitude":-3.083,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nEda was born about 1240. \n\nEdna Crichton was born 1240 in Crichton Castle, Pathhead, East Lothian, Scotland, and died date unknown.\n\nShe married Thomas De Crichton on 1258 in Crichton Castle, Pathhead, East Lothian, Scotland, son of Thurston De Crichton.\n\n«b»Children of Edna Crichton and Thomas De Crichton are:«/b»\n1.) Nicholas Crichton, b. 1264, Crichton Castle, Pathhead, East Lothian, Scotland, d. 1340\n\n2.) William de CRICHTON , 1st Laird of Sanquhar b: ABT 1270 in Crichton Castle, Pathhead, East Lothian, Scotland","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1240","date":"Abt 1240","place":"Pathhead, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1258","date":"1258","place":"Pathhead, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","type":"Spousal","age":"18","id":"GVFZ-DC2"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1265","date":"Abt 1265","place":"Pathhead, Midlothian, Scotland","age":"25","id":"K1T8-NTT"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1270","date":"about 1270","place":"Crichton Castle, East Lothian, Scotland","age":"30","id":"GNYP-4HJ"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1283","date":"1283","place":"Pathead, Midlothian, Sco